<blockquote>
<h2>Welcome</h2>

<h3>Seminar Discussion Thread</h3><p> 

Last Append: Tue Jul 23 09:45:03 1996<p>

Welcome to "SUMMER IN ATLANTA: 100 YEARS OF SPORTS LAW!"<p>  

Counsel Connect has gathered a panel of experts (see the thread MEET THE
PANELISTS) to discuss a variety of amateur sports law issues in this
two-week seminar from July 22 to August 2.  What's nice about this seminar,
of course, is that it will take place during the Olympic Games themselves. 
The Games will provide a fitting, moving backdrop for our discussion of
current-day amateur sports law issues.<p>   

The range of topics for this seminar is wide-open.  Any amateur sports law
issue is up for grabs.  Whether it's the IOC's use of arbitration for
athlete disputes, the role "ambush marketing" plays during the Games, or
whether a minimum age for amateur athletes should be required, all relevant
discussion is encouraged.  In addition, interactions and comparisons
between amateur and professional athletics are also fair game, as are
discussions on excessive corporate sponsorship and relevant municipal
concerns.  As you can see, the canvas is wide and open to
interpretation.<p>  

I hope you'll join us.<p>

Let the legal games begin!<p>

Todd Drucker<br>
Counsel Connect Law Editor<p>


<H3><a href="/spotlight/games/"><I>Back</I></a></H3>


