<P>Appended by: Maria Dennis -- Jones Day - Los Angeles<BR> Date: Tue Jul 23
14:42:05 1996 <BR>Subject: Ice Hockey </P>

<P>Just to update everyone, the national governing body of ice hockey, USA
Hockey (of which I am a Board member) is sending its DREAM TEAM to the 1998
Winter Olympics due to the cooperation of the National Hockey League, which
will suspend its professional season for two weeks in order to allow the
best players in the world to compete in the Olympics. </P>

<P>While I am sad that "amateurs" (mostly college players) will not be able to
go to the Olympics for men's ice hockey, I am reminded by a fellow Board
member that our US men's team will be comprised of players who grew up
through the amateur ranks of USA Hockey.  It is not like they are some
other classification of human being--they were all amateurs at one time.   </P>

<P>-Maria Dennis, Co-Moderator</P>
