I sorta feel sorry about the teams whose country can't afford uniforms, like Lithuania. And the uniforms that don't fit. A good friend and former beau is the chief coach for the Russian Federation wrestling team, and the money that used to go to them and their training is down dramatically. Somehow, putting dream team professional, no holds barred, no costs spared athletes against these guys seems unfair. Computer training, aero dynamic design of equipment and uniforms...special diets...seems like we're putting our thumb too heavily on the scale.<p> 

<hr><p>


Appended by: Greg Ross -- Poyner & Spruill - Charlotte<br> 
Date: Mon Jul 29 10:41:44 1996<br> 
