Wow -- Melanie's "dog abuse" analogy is incredibly powerful and right on the money for me.  I watched more of the recaps last night, and I just can't shake this feeling that something is not right.<p>  

And with all due respect, I just don't buy the argument that this is about sexism. I would feel *exactly* the same way about coaches pushing young male ball players.  And speaking of boxing, I am utterly repelled by boxing -- I don't see any value in beating people up for sport.  It glorifies violence and destruction.<p>  

While I resonate to the arguments about the positive values of "going for the gold," and the related positive values of health, teamwork, etc., I also think there is a dangerous undercurrent  when those goals turn into obsessions.  And after watching the reports about Bella, and watching the interviews, I am not convinced that his interactions with most of these girls are, in the long run, positive.  Yes, the gal in question is 18, and that is a BIG difference. But still.  I urge anybody who finds this discussion intriguing to buy Joan Ryan's book -- or find someone with a video of her 60 Minutes video.  It puts a lot of this into perspective.<p>   

