You're right on the money regarding referring to any child as a "cow" -- that is certainly abusive.  Someone up the thread, however, raised an excellent point regarding the depression/suicide rate among young female gymnasts vs. the rate among the general young female population.  For  girls reaching adolescence, the incidence of depression is enormous.  To anyone who has a teenage daughter (as I do), or is otherwise interested, I highly recommend a book called "Reviving Ophelia:  Saving the Selves of Adolescent Girls," by Mary Pipher.  It's not just the Belas of the world, it's society in general, and hormones, and everything else.  I'm not ready to say that Bela is the monster that some make him out to be -- but I just know that I wouldn't subject my daughter to that kind of regimen.<p> 

