So, now, what if there *had* been an "Amicus Puerae" or an "Arbitrator Medicalis Puerae" and the independent ruling had been that Strugg should not vault a second time due to her injury?  The chances are excellent that she would have been in position to win **2** more gold medals for the good ole US of A, in the individual vault and the individual floor competitions.  However, due to the severity of the injury aggravated by her second vault, which was *unnecessary* to win the team gold medal, she now cannot even *compete* for these two gold medals.  I say a loss to Kerri, and a loss to her country.<p> 

