Appended by: Susan Nogan -- CC Law Editor - Washington <BR>Date: Mon Aug  5 12:54:31 1996 <BR>Subject: Footnote 
<BR><BR>
Did anyone else see the irony in the background of one of the US divers.  (Can't recall her name, but I think she's about 14, compared to 30-something Mary Ellen Clark.) 
<BR><BR>
She started out as a gymnast with Bela Karolyi, but had to retire when she developed a stress fracture in her back (!) at the age of 8 (!).  Announcers could only comment on how fortunate for all that her parents found another sport for her to compete in (!), and Cynthia Potter (who was marvelous, by the way) pointed out that persistent back pain has interfered with her training, and also with her execution at these Olympics. 
<BR><BR>
It's clear (to me at least) that their daughter's health is not of primary concern to these parents.   


<BR><BR> 

<hr><BR><BR>

