<blockquote>
<h2>Islamic Women Athletes</h2>

<h3>Seminar Discussion Thread</h3><p> 

Do the Olympic rules in any way address gender discrimination by participating countries that prevent women from competing in women's events?<p> 

Unless I'm mistaken, during the opening ceremonies last Friday, as the Saudi team came into the stadium, I heard the NBC commentator note that in some Muslim countries women were barred from competing in certain sports because the athletic attire required for those events would violate Islamic law.<p> 

I don't know how fundamentalist Muslim women feel about wearing track shorts or bathing suits.  But to the extent they want to compete, are there any international protections for women seeking to freely participate in the Games?<p> 

Jesse<p>

