<h2>Seeking Asylum in Atlanta</h2>

<h3>Seminar Discussion Thread</h3><p> 

From: Todd Drucker -- CC- Law Editor - New York<BR>
Date: Thu Aug  1 12:46:29 1996<BR>
Subject: Seeking Asylum in Atlanta

<BR><BR>


Raed Ahmed, an Iraqi weight lifter, walked out of the Olympic village
yesterday and asked for political asylum in the U.S.. 
<BR><BR>
Ahmed became the first non-Cuban athlete to defect during the Games.  In
recent weeks, the Cuban team has lost two baseball players, two boxers,
and one boxing coach (who was on loan to Mexico). 
<BR><BR>
Does anyone know how the IOC, ACOG and the Immigration and
Naturalization Service is working together to handle these defections? 
Is there a special office set up?  Does the IOC have a policy (said or
unsaid), encouraging or discouraging visiting athletes from defecting?  


